8522  }
8523  }
8524  }
8525  }
8526  p1 = p1->shape->proto;
8527  prototype_lookup:
8528  if (!p1)
8529  break;
8530 
8531  retry2:
8532  prs = find_own_property(&pr, p1, prop);
8533  if (prs) {
8534  if ((prs->flags & JS_PROP_TMASK) == JS_PROP_GETSET) {
8535  return call_setter(ctx, pr->u.getset.setter, this_obj, val, flags);
8536  } else if ((prs->flags & JS_PROP_TMASK) == JS_PROP_AUTOINIT) {
8537  /* Instantiate property and retry (potentially useless) */
8538  if (JS_AutoInitProperty(ctx, p1, prop, pr, prs))
8539  return -1;
8540  goto retry2;
8541  } else if (!(prs->flags & JS_PROP_WRITABLE)) {
8542  read_only_prop:
8543  JS_FreeValue(ctx, val);
8544  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorReadOnly(ctx, flags, prop);
8545  }
8546  }
8547  }
8548 
8549  if (unlikely(flags & JS_PROP_NO_ADD)) {
8550  JS_FreeValue(ctx, val);
8551  JS_ThrowReferenceErrorNotDefined(ctx, prop);
8552  return -1;
8553  }
8554 
8555  if (unlikely(!p)) {
8556  JS_FreeValue(ctx, val);
8557  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "not an object");
8558  }
8559 
8560  if (unlikely(!p->extensible)) {
8561  JS_FreeValue(ctx, val);
8562  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "object is not extensible");
8563  }
8564 
8565  if (p->is_exotic) {
8566  if (p->class_id == JS_CLASS_ARRAY && p->fast_array &&
8567  __JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop)) {
8568  uint32_t idx = __JS_AtomToUInt32(prop);
8569  if (idx == p->u.array.count) {
8570  /* fast case */
8571  return add_fast_array_element(ctx, p, val, flags);
8572  } else {
8573  goto generic_create_prop;
8574  }
8575  } else {
8576  generic_create_prop:
8577  ret = JS_CreateProperty(ctx, p, prop, val, JS_UNDEFINED, JS_UNDEFINED,
8578  flags |
8579  JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE |
8580  JS_PROP_HAS_ENUMERABLE |
8581  JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE |
8582  JS_PROP_HAS_CONFIGURABLE |
8583  JS_PROP_C_W_E);
8584  JS_FreeValue(ctx, val);
8585  return ret;
8586  }
8587  }
8588 
8589  pr = add_property(ctx, p, prop, JS_PROP_C_W_E);
8590  if (unlikely(!pr)) {
8591  JS_FreeValue(ctx, val);
8592  return -1;
8593  }
8594  pr->u.value = val;
8595  return TRUE;
8596 }

9089  if (!js_same_value(ctx, val, pr->u.value)) {
9090  goto not_configurable;
9091  } else {
9092  return TRUE;
9093  }
9094  }
9095  }
9096  if ((prs->flags & JS_PROP_TMASK) == JS_PROP_VARREF) {
9097  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9098  if (p->class_id == JS_CLASS_MODULE_NS) {
9099  /* JS_PROP_WRITABLE is always true for variable
9100  references, but they are write protected in module name
9101  spaces. */
9102  if (!js_same_value(ctx, val, *pr->u.var_ref->pvalue))
9103  goto not_configurable;
9104  }
9105  /* update the reference */
9106  set_value(ctx, pr->u.var_ref->pvalue,
9107  JS_DupValue(ctx, val));
9108  }
9109  /* if writable is set to false, no longer a
9110  reference (for mapped arguments) */
9111  if ((flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE)) == JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE) {
9112  JSValue val1;
9113  if (js_shape_prepare_update(ctx, p, &prs))
9114  return -1;
9115  val1 = JS_DupValue(ctx, *pr->u.var_ref->pvalue);
9116  free_var_ref(ctx->rt, pr->u.var_ref);
9117  pr->u.value = val1;
9118  prs->flags &= ~(JS_PROP_TMASK | JS_PROP_WRITABLE);
9119  }
9120  } else if (prs->flags & JS_PROP_LENGTH) {
9121  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9122  /* Note: no JS code is executable because
9123  'val' is guaranted to be a Uint32 */
9124  res = set_array_length(ctx, p, JS_DupValue(ctx, val),
9125  flags);
9126  } else {
9127  res = TRUE;
9128  }
9129  /* still need to reset the writable flag if
9130  needed. The JS_PROP_LENGTH is kept because the
9131  Uint32 test is still done if the length
9132  property is read-only. */
9133  if ((flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE)) ==
9134  JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE) {
9135  prs = get_shape_prop(p->shape);
9136  if (js_update_property_flags(ctx, p, &prs,
9137  prs->flags & ~JS_PROP_WRITABLE))
9138  return -1;
9139  }
9140  return res;
9141  } else {
9142  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9143  JS_FreeValue(ctx, pr->u.value);
9144  pr->u.value = JS_DupValue(ctx, val);
9145  }
9146  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE) {
9147  if (js_update_property_flags(ctx, p, &prs,
9148  (prs->flags & ~JS_PROP_WRITABLE) |
9149  (flags & JS_PROP_WRITABLE)))
9150  return -1;
9151  }
9152  }
9153  }
9154  }
9155  mask = 0;
9156  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_CONFIGURABLE)
9157  mask |= JS_PROP_CONFIGURABLE;
9158  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_ENUMERABLE)
9159  mask |= JS_PROP_ENUMERABLE;
9160  if (js_update_property_flags(ctx, p, &prs,
9161  (prs->flags & ~mask) | (flags & mask)))
9162  return -1;
9163  return TRUE;
9164  }
9165 
9166  /* handle modification of fast array elements */
9167  if (p->fast_array) {
9168  uint32_t idx;
9169  uint32_t prop_flags;
9170  if (p->class_id == JS_CLASS_ARRAY) {
9171  if (__JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop)) {
9172  idx = __JS_AtomToUInt32(prop);
9173  if (idx < p->u.array.count) {
9174  prop_flags = get_prop_flags(flags, JS_PROP_C_W_E);
9175  if (prop_flags != JS_PROP_C_W_E)
9176  goto convert_to_slow_array;
9177  if (flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_GET | JS_PROP_HAS_SET)) {
9178  convert_to_slow_array:
9179  if (convert_fast_array_to_array(ctx, p))
9180  return -1;
9181  else
9182  goto redo_prop_update;
9183  }
9184  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9185  set_value(ctx, &p->u.array.u.values[idx], JS_DupValue(ctx, val));
9186  }
9187  return TRUE;
9188  }
9189  }
9190  } else if (p->class_id >= JS_CLASS_UINT8C_ARRAY &&
9191  p->class_id <= JS_CLASS_FLOAT64_ARRAY) {
9192  JSValue num;
9193  int ret;
9194 
9195  if (!__JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop)) {
9196  /* slow path with to handle all numeric indexes */
9197  num = JS_AtomIsNumericIndex1(ctx, prop);
9198  if (JS_IsUndefined(num))
9199  goto typed_array_done;
9200  if (JS_IsException(num))
9201  return -1;
9202  ret = JS_NumberIsInteger(ctx, num);
9203  if (ret < 0) {
9204  JS_FreeValue(ctx, num);
9205  return -1;
9206  }
9207  if (!ret) {
9208  JS_FreeValue(ctx, num);
9209  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "non integer index in typed array");
9210  }
9211  ret = JS_NumberIsNegativeOrMinusZero(ctx, num);
9212  JS_FreeValue(ctx, num);
9213  if (ret) {
9214  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "negative index in typed array");
9215  }
9216  if (!__JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop))
9217  goto typed_array_oob;
9218  }
9219  idx = __JS_AtomToUInt32(prop);
9220  /* if the typed array is detached, p->u.array.count = 0 */
9221  if (idx >= typed_array_get_length(ctx, p)) {
9222  typed_array_oob:
9223  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "out-of-bound index in typed array");
9224  }
9225  prop_flags = get_prop_flags(flags, JS_PROP_ENUMERABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE | JS_PROP_CONFIGURABLE);
9226  if (flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_GET | JS_PROP_HAS_SET) ||
9227  prop_flags != (JS_PROP_ENUMERABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE | JS_PROP_CONFIGURABLE)) {
9228  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "invalid descriptor flags");
9229  }
9230  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9231  return JS_SetPropertyValue(ctx, this_obj, JS_NewInt32(ctx, idx), JS_DupValue(ctx, val), flags);
9232  }
9233  return TRUE;
9234  typed_array_done: ;
9235  }
9236  }
9237 
9238  return JS_CreateProperty(ctx, p, prop, val, getter, setter, flags);
9239 }
